      <dsc>
         <c id="ref10" level="series">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Inventory, 1933-1997</unittitle>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_89649665c18735d4db8a28e48aacd576">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The papers consist of correspondence, journals, research notes, photographs, scrapbooks and memorabilia related to Herbert Warren Wind's personal life and career as a writer and sports journalist. Correspondence is incoming and generally concerns Wind's articles and books. Many of the letters are from notable sports figures such as Ben Hogan, Gene Sarazen, and the Jack Nicklaus family as well as literary figures such as P.G. Wodehouse and John Updike. Research notes, manuscripts and photographs mainly relate to Wind's articles and books about golf, although some manuscripts are drafts of fictional works, probably unpublished.</p>
            </scopecontent>
